    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - ASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Inspect tension spring, washer, and spade pin bores for wear. Replace if necessary.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Apply oil to the shift lever pivot ball and housing socket prior to assembly. Refer to GROUP
                        10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended lubes.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Seat the tension spring one coil at a time.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the assembly in a vise with the bottom of the housing facing up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302696">Figure 96</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302696" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302696" filename="../figg13/g1302696.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 96. Secure Assembly in Vise and Inspect Housing Tower Spade Pins and Spade Pin
                        Bores
                    </caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If housing tower spade pin bores are worn, discard the housing tower and replace with a
                    new housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302696">Figure 96</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the spade pins are damaged, replace and install the spade pins in the housing tower
                    bore (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302696">Figure 96</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the lever ball slot with the spade pin and position the gear shift lever in the
                    housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302697">Figure 97</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302697" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302697" filename="../figg13/g1302697.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 97. Position Gear Shift Lever in Housing Tower and Install Washer Over Ball
                    </caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the washer over the ball with dished side up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302697">Figure 97</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a tension spring driver to install the tension spring under the housing lugs (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302698">Figure 98</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302698" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302698" filename="../figg13/g1302698.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 98. Install Tension Spring Under Housing Lugs</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the assembly from the vise (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302699">Figure 99</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302699" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302699" filename="../figg13/g1302699.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 99. Remove Assembly From Vise and Install Rubber Boot Over Gear Shift Lever
                    </caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a rubber boot over the gear shift lever and against the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302699">Figure 99</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the shift lever grip.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
